{"parentUuid":"0efcd5ce-166f-48a3-bd7d-8224e99ef1f6","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccrt2SJshLKeuVTd7TKWz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018HG8pjVdCN14LTKtuydfpU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21261,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21261,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccrt2QNYdJ5UkG8Lkjifg","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"a08ad77e-41e1-4c87-bc82-7d37316076a8","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:30:26.013Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"a08ad77e-41e1-4c87-bc82-7d37316076a8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018HG8pjVdCN14LTKtuydfpU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — usage CSV export\n2\t\n3\tElicited 2026-07-09 (operator interview, pre-planning). Brief: PROJECT.md (GET /v1/usage/export,\n4\tcaller's rollups as CSV, existing API-key auth, no behavior change to existing endpoints,\n5\tno design source).\n6\t\n7\t## Resolved\n8\t\n9\t- What rows does the export return? → Every `usage_rollup` row under the authenticated\n10\t  `api_key_id`, with **optional** `customer_id` and `metric` query filters (reusing the\n11\t  existing validated types). No required params.\n12\t- Time-range semantics? → Optional `from`/`to` aware-datetime params, validated like the\n13\t  existing window bound (`from <= to`, both within `[now−90d, now+1h]`); omitted → the full\n14\t  supported range. Naive datetimes rejected (existing idiom).\n15\t- Size control? → **Streaming** response (constant memory, rows written as read) with a\n16\t  **hard cap of 100,000 rows**; a result exceeding the cap fails 422 `validation_failed`\n17\t  telling the caller to narrow filters. No pagination this slice.\n18\t- Who may export? → **Any authenticated key** (ingest or admin) — it is the caller's own\n19\t  tenant data, same read authority as GET /v1/usage; normal edge stack\n20\t  (require_api_key → Tier-2 per-key throttle).\n21\t- CSV formula injection? → **Escape formula-leading text cells** at the CSV-encoding\n22\t  boundary (OWASP defense: prefix `'` when a text cell starts with `=`, `+`, `-`, `@`,\n23\t  incl. tab/CR variants; control chars stripped/quoted). Numeric/timestamp columns untouched.\n24\t- Response headers? → `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8` +\n25\t  `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv`\n26\t  (no tenant identifiers in the filename).\n27\t- Dialect? → RFC 4180 via the stdlib csv module (no hand-rolled encoder): header row always\n28\t  present, exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief's column order);\n29\t  CRLF line endings; quote fields containing comma/quote/newline.\n30\t- Empty result? → **200 with a header-only CSV** (one shape for consumers; mirrors the\n31\t  existing zeros-not-404 contract).\n32\t- Ordering? → Deterministic `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC` (index-friendly;\n33\t  identical exports diff cleanly).\n34\t- Value formats? → `window_start` as the UTC ISO-8601 string with offset (identical to the\n35\t  JSON response's string form); `total_quantity` as a plain decimal string via `str(Decimal)`\n36\t  (no scientific notation).\n37\t- Perf posture? → Reporting route: **documented p95 target, NOT a k6 load AC** (proposed\n38\t  default: p95 < 500 ms at the 100k-row cap, verified by an integration timing sanity check).\n39\t  The binding perf criterion is negative: POST /v1/events' existing budget, tests, and code\n40\t  path are untouched (the brief's own no-behavior-change constraint).\n41\t- New stored data? → None — read-only feature over existing rollups; no migration, no new\n42\t  data-classification surface.\n43\t\n44\t## Open\n45\t\n46\t- The exact documented p95 target number for the export route (500 ms at the cap was the\n47\t  proposed default; low stakes — planning states a default or raises it at the checkpoint).\n48\t\n49\t## Out of scope\n50\t\n51\t- Pagination (`limit`/`offset`) — the row cap + filters are the size control this slice.\n52\t- Admin-only gating of exports — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data.\n53\t- Other formats (JSON export, XLSX), compression (gzip), and scheduled/async export jobs.\n54\t- Any change to GET /v1/usage, POST /v1/events, PUT /v1/quotas, or their budgets/tests.\n55\t- Per-export audit logging beyond the standard structured request log.\n56\t"}]},"u