{"parentUuid":"a649fd93-3983-47f8-9f96-31d982daee40","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcruCDgW4czNYLaDy9UCc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GPxDZcGqXE3n4ycMFFTjp3","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan-audit.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":136154,"cache_read_input_tokens":15955,"output_tokens":399,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":136154},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":399,"cache_read_input_tokens":15955,"cache_creation_input_tokens":136154,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":136154,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"unavailable"}}},"requestId":"req_011CcruCBwpgUHhMVe7tAiTy","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"b2a7bc1e-2a7f-4690-bf0a-2455268f660f","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:45:45.621Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"b2a7bc1e-2a7f-4690-bf0a-2455268f660f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GPxDZcGqXE3n4ycMFFTjp3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\taudited_at: 2026-07-09T17:44:24Z\n3\tplan_sha256: d62171b60ab0f155a7d2020fba19bfdaf1ce403060cf9cfcfb74af0993ea1e8f\n4\tflags_total: 2\n5\tmaterial_flags: 2\n6\tcritical_flags: 0\n7\trevision_recommended: true\n8\tdependencies_checked: 0\n9\tdependencies_unverified: 0\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\t# Plan audit — usage CSV export (`GET /v1/usage/export`)\n13\t\n14\t## Focus here first\n15\t\n16\t- **[material]** `tasks.md` was not emitted, but the plan's own trigger is met: `criteria_total: 21`\n17\t  in `.pipeline/acceptance.md` is **≥ the 15-criteria decomposition threshold**, independent of the\n18\t  14-file count. The plan's frontmatter comment (\"change set ~14 files, below the >=25-file\n19\t  decomposition trigger\") only checks the file-count leg of the OR and is silent on the\n20\t  criteria-count leg — so the no-decomposition call is unjustified against the stated policy.\n21\t  This blocks the implementation agent from a traceable per-task AC map on a feature with 21\n22\t  acceptance criteria and 7 distinct layers/modules touched.\n23\t- **[material]** No `acceptance.md` criterion covers a forced internal-server error returning the\n24\t  generic error-envelope with no partial side effect (ASVS-DET T2-2 safe-error shape), for the\n25\t  feature's own new server-side error surface — specifically the pre-flight `prepare_export`\n26\t  `COUNT(*)` phase, which runs *before* any response bytes are sent and so *can* still cleanly\n27\t  return the standard envelope on a DB error. The plan's **R3** accepted risk only excuses the\n28\t  *post-200, mid-stream* truncation case (correctly, since the envelope can't apply after body\n29\t  bytes are sent) — it does not address the pre-flight phase, and no AC exercises \"prepare_export\n30\t  raises a raw DB error → generic `internal_error` envelope, not a leaked stack/SQL, and no\n31\t  streaming started.\"\n32\t- No other blocking concerns. Ambiguity audit is clean, STRIDE mechanisms all name a concrete\n33\t  file + call, the ASVS Compliance block is present and scoped, the repomix receipt is present and\n34\t  its sha matches disk, and the plan introduces no new third-party dependency.\n35\t\n36\t## Completeness\n37\t\n38\t| Dimension | Status | Missing item | Blocks which agent | material/advisory |\n39\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n40\t| Layer sections present | ✓ | — | — | — |\n41\t| Acceptance criteria traced | ✓ | `.pipeline/acceptance.md` exists, 21 criteria, each traced to a file/layer and a verification method; brief's one Open item carried with a proposed default | — | — |\n42\t| Task decomposition coverage (TA/A-3) | gap | `tasks.md` not emitted despite `criteria_total: 21` meeting the \"≥15 criteria\" OR-trigger (file count alone, 14, is under the 25 threshold, but the criteria leg is independently sufficient) | implementation (no per-task AC traceability map on a 21-criterion, 7-layer change) | material |\n43\t| STRIDE mechanisms named | ✓ | Every threat row names a concrete mechanism + file (e.g. `escape_csv_text_cell` / `src/api/csv_export.py`, bound-parameter SQL + fixed-literal ORDER BY / `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`) | — | — |\n44\t| Input-surface controls complete | ✓ | One input source (query params) declared with both a non-waivable validation criterion (AC4) and a correctly principal-keyed post-auth rate-limit criterion (AC5, Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`) | — | — |\n45\t| Data-protection complete | n/a | `new_stored_data: false` — read-only feature over an existing table, no new stored field to classify | — | — |\n46\t| Object-level authorization tested | ✓ | No client-supplied resource id; the export is scoped wholesale to the caller's own `api_key_id`. AC7 asserts cross-tenant denial (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) — the IDOR-equivalent shape for this access pattern | — | — |\n47\t| Authentication boundary tested | ✓ | AC6: unauthenticated/invalid key → 401, tested | — | — |\n48\t| Safe-error handling tested | gap | No AC covers a forced internal error in the pre-flight (`prepare_export`) phase returning the generic envelope / failing closed before any body byte is sent; R3 only excuses the post-200 mid-stream case | testing (no test exercises the still-cleanly-recoverable failure path); security (T2-2 reconciliation) | material |\n49\t| Security-property tests (T2-3…T2-6) | n/a | No self-contained tokens issued/consumed, no session management, no multi-write/money operation, no password registration in this feature | — | — |\n50\t| App-store submission criteria | n/a | No store target declared in `PROJECT.md` | — | — |\n51\t| DAST readiness | ✓ | AC19 (served OpenAPI schema incl. route+responses), AC20 (seeded test key), AC21 (Bearer auth-context shape documented) all present | — | — |\n52\t| ASVS compliance scoped | ✓ | `## ASVS Compliance` block present: triggered chapters listed, L3 explicitly \"none new,\" L1/L2 waivers named with reasons | — | — |\n53\t| Test strategy declared | ✓ | `pyramid`, default, brief rationale for the unit/integration split given | — | — |\n54\t| Files affected concrete | ✓ | Concrete paths + one-line reason each, matching per-layer sections | — | — |\n55\t| Repomix receipt (F-M4-6) | ✓ | `repomix_pack_sha256` in frontmatter matches `sha256sum .pipeline/repomix-pack.xml` on disk (`67eadd30...83de68`) | — | — |\n56\t\n57\t## Ambiguities\n58\t\n59\tNone found. The plan is concretely specified throughout: every endpoint carries its method/path,\n60\tevery schema field its type and bound, every error path its status code and envelope shape, and no\n61\t`TODO`/`TBD`/placeholder markers survive. No internal contradictions were found (data store,\n62\tconcurrency model, and streaming approach are stated once and consistent across sections).\n63\t\n64\t## Proof-claim verification (3b)\n65\t\n66\tNo unenforced \"provably/guaranteed/invariant\" style claims found. The three uses of\n67\t\"invariant(s)\"/\"guarantee\" in the plan (no-change guarantee via an untouched file, the two\n68\tstreaming invariants kept alive by opening the transaction inside the generator, and the\n69\trow-level-security invariant of scoping every query by `api_key_id` first) are each backed by a\n70\tconcrete enforcement point already covered in the completeness/STRIDE tables (an untouched file is\n71\tdirectly diff-checkable; the transaction-in-generator structure is the code itself; the\n72\t`api_key_id` filter is asserted by AC7's cross-tenant integration test). None is a bare assertion\n73\tresting on an unstated or unenforced condition.\n74\t\n75\t## Cross-feature data-flow trace (3c)\n76\t\n77\tThis feature reads `usage_rollup`, written by the existing ingestion path (`POST /v1/events`,\n78\tfeature 1) and already read successfully by `GET /v1/usage` (feature 2's sibling endpoint). The\n79\texport scopes every query by `api_key_id = principal.api_key_id` — the same join key ingestion\n80\twrites under and the same key `GET /v1/usage` already reads by. No principal/scope mismatch of the\n81\tfeature-3 shape (reading with a key that ingests nothing) is present.\n82\t\n83\t## Dependency reality\n84\t\n85\tNo new dependencies. The plan reuses only packages already pinned in `pyproject.toml`\n86\t(fastapi, starlette, sqlalchemy, pydantic, structlog, etc.) plus Python stdlib (`csv`, `io`,\n87\t`decimal`). No new line is added to `pyproject.toml` or `poetry.lock` in Files affected.\n88\t\n89\t## Version policy\n90\t\n91\tNo new dependencies — table not applicable.\n92\t\n93\t## Could not verify\n94\t\n95\tNone — no registry lookups were required (no new dependency), and no other item in this audit\n96\tdepended on network access.\n97\t"}]},"uuid":"56d0cfa5-fdb6-4ad4-a389-a75e80e2b160","timestamp"