{"parentUuid":"8e8065e5-7714-440e-bd02-f970200b51cd","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcruFMMhPc1EighwGBwsz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011iqHTXf9g17SiaARZqeJK5","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan.md","offset":96,"limit":18},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":157287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":670,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcruFKwcuHQBC5WtzkrKR","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"02b77d86-c281-4d96-8328-171174c3c917","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:46:23.396Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"02b77d86-c281-4d96-8328-171174c3c917","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011iqHTXf9g17SiaARZqeJK5","type":"tool_result","content":"96\t  authenticated key may export — brief resolved).\n97\t\n98\tThe handler is deliberately two-phase to make the row cap a clean pre-body 422:\n99\t\n100\t1. **Pre-flight cap check (still a normal request, can 422 cleanly).** Call the service's\n101\t   `prepare_export(principal, params)`, which runs a `COUNT(*)` with the same filters inside\n102\t   a tenant-scoped transaction and raises `HTTPException(status_code=422, detail=...)` if the\n103\t   count exceeds 100,000. 422 already maps to `validation_failed` in `src/api/errors.py`'s\n104\t   `_STATUS_TO_CODE`, so this needs no `AppError` — a plain `HTTPException(422)` yields the\n105\t   brief-required `{\"error\":{\"code\":\"validation_failed\",...}}` envelope. *Why a pre-flight\n106\t   count and not \"stream until the 100,001st row\":* once we return a `StreamingResponse` the\n107\t   status line is already `200` and the first bytes may be on the wire — we cannot retro-send\n108\t   a 422. The cap decision must therefore precede any response body. The count is an\n109\t   index-prefix scan over the caller's `api_key_id` and is cheap.\n110\t2. **Stream.** Return `StreamingResponse(stream_export_csv(principal, params),\n111\t   media_type=\"text/csv; charset=utf-8\", headers={\"Content-Disposition\": 'attachment;\n112\t   filename=\"usage-export-<UTC>.csv\"'})`. The generator is consumed by Starlette *after* the\n113\t   handler returns, so it opens its **own** tenant-scoped transaction (see below)."}]},"uuid":"1eef47e9-c9db-4b11-a71c-e034b77e4ff6","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:46:23.412Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"02b77d86-c281-4d96-8328-171174c3c917","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
