{"parentUuid":"7a92e112-6a2d-454b-9abc-5afa2d431cf0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MZGby2UrWTzzJwNmgRJ9QL","type":"tool_result","content":"148\t  \"total_quantity\")`.\n149\t- `async def prepare_export(principal, params) -> None` — opens `scoped_transaction(\n150\t  principal.api_key_id)`, calls `count_usage_rollups(...)`, raises `HTTPException(422,\n151\t  \"result exceeds 100000 rows; narrow with customer_id, metric, from, and/or to\")` when over\n152\t  cap; logs the rejection at `warn` (`usage.export.rejected`, `reason=\"row_cap_exceeded\"`).\n153\t- `async def stream_export_csv(principal, params) -> AsyncIterator[bytes]` — the body\n154\t  generator. *This is the load-bearing streaming design:*\n155\t  - It opens its **own** `scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id)` and does all DB work\n156\t    inside it. *Why inside the generator, not the handler:* Starlette pulls the generator\n157\t    after the handler returns, so a transaction opened in the handler would already be closed"}]},"uuid":"fb3e6036-aa42-4aff-bd90-c7600f8524ff","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:46:24.034Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7a92e112-6a2d-454b-9abc-5afa2d431cf0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
