{"parentUuid":"0c38473f-6699-418a-a4eb-95138ac52935","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"53f5148a-6791-4be6-a2fc-f4eaf65be586","agentId":"aab619a6f776136ee","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KB7CHXAd3xzHiAhT13bLFN","type":"tool_result","content":"488\t  role; isolation rests on the explicit `api_key_id` filter. Pre-existing, affects `GET /v1/usage`\n489\t  equally; follow-up migration recommended (Open Q3), not built here.\n490\t- **R3 — mid-stream failure truncates the CSV** rather than returning a clean error envelope: once\n491\t  200 + body bytes are sent, the envelope can't apply. Accepted: the dominant failure mode\n492\t  (oversized result) is caught cleanly by the pre-flight 422; a rare mid-stream DB error yields a\n493\t  truncated download the client re-requests. Out of scope: CSV trailer/checksum.\n494\t- Out of scope per the brief (not threats, exclusions): pagination, admin-only gating, other\n495\t  formats/compression/async export jobs, any change to existing endpoints, per-export audit\n496\t  logging beyond the one structured event above.\n497\t\n498\t### Threat-model diagram (Mermaid DFD)\n499\t"}]},"uuid":"a6365902-b50b-4935-9b4f-a02833caf3e6","timestamp":"2026-07-09T17:46:24.908Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0c38473f-6699-418a-a4eb-95138ac52935","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
