\t| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n20\t| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n21\t| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n22\t| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n23\t| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n24\t| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n25\t| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n26\t| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n27\t| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n28\t| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n29\t| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n30\t| AC15 | No behavior change: `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, `PUT /v1/quotas` behavior/budgets/tests unchanged; no new Alembic revision / migration added | repo-wide (negative) | Existing test suites pass unchanged; no new file under `alembic/versions/` |\n31\t| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 < 500 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (documented target, integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows |\n32\t| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, 